The All Progressives Congress (APC) has released names of members of the committee to screen Edo governorship aspirants. The party also named Appeal Committee members. The list was released on Tuesday by Edegbe Odemwingie, APC Assistant Director of Publicity. On the Screening Committee are Prof. Jonathan Ayuba (Chairman), Prof. Agbo Madaki, Hon. Ibrahim Zailani, Sen. Aishatu Dahiru Ahmed, Dr. Jane Frances Agbu, Hon. Fort Dike and Dr. Rabe Nasir (Secretary). Members of the Appeal Committee Dr. Abubakar Fari (Chairman), Prof. Sadeeque Abba, Barr. Gbenga Olubajo, Mohammed Idris, Esther Bepeh and Barr. Daniel Bwala (Secretary). The party had announced that six aspirants will be screened ahead of its primary election. The hopefuls Governor Godwin Obaseki, Osagie Ize-Iyamu, Pius Odubu, Chris Ogiemwonyi, Osaro Obazee and Matthew Aigbuhuenze Iduoriyekemwen. The APC primary election has been slated for Monday, June 22, while the appeal will hold on Wednesday, June 24.